@node read "Intro:"
                                     Intro:

        Basically this is a tool where you can set A Listview to hold as
                          many Lines of text you need.
          you double click the ListItem to set the Current Clipboard.


 Then you can press the Right_Amiga-V to Paste the text into anywhere possible

              Using the Characters '%n' causes a LineFeed <Return>


     This was originally written For AmIRC to be able to store preset Texts
         (Like it's FKey Settings) and Paste into the window with ease.

Now i've added a few features like ..

      Prefs file argument/Tooltype: to load a different config at startup.

      A chooser gadget lets you cycle to different lists (up to 48 Pages)

                Append MUI textstyles (colour Bold ect) to Texts

                     Bubble Help instead of Screen TitleBar

Saving @{" Settings " link prefs} Saves ...
   Window positions.
   Current Page position.
   If an item is selected this is remembered and auto pasted at each startup.
Also take 2 minutes to read @{" Important things to know: " link imp}

@endnode

@node imp "Important things to know:"


                           Important things to know:
                            -------------------------

   For AmIRC if AmIRC is already running and you don't have Clipper installed
       you will have to reload in order to see Clipper.amirx in the Menus


                                     ALSO.

       I added a function to insert MUI TextInput codes (colour Bold ect)

     Due to a restriction i cannot get a cursor position of the text gadget
       to "insert" text at cursor pos (it's added to the end of the text)


                                     ALSO.

     You MUST press <return> after entering ANY text (not the menu inserts)
                           or Changes will be erased

@endnode

@node runing "Running Clipper"


                                Running from WB:


                 Just double click the icon and away you go :)





                               Running from CLI:

              Currently there is 2 arguments that can be supplied

                   Syntax:  rx Clipper <filename> SCREEN=Name

                             Do NOT use Quotes '"'

           if filename is omited then S:ClipPrefs/Clipper.cfg is used

         if Screen=Name is omited then Intuition's ActiveScreen is used

                    rx is optional as the script flag is set
                           you'd probably want to use

                    "Clipper"

                 OR "run >nil: Clipper s:ClipPrefs/another.cfg"

                 OR "Clipper s:ClipPrefs/another.cfg screen AWeb"


@endnode
@node use "Usage"


                                     Usage:


                   Double Click a text to set the clipboard.

             Select Show Edit Gadgets from the menu to edit the GUI

                   See @{" Prefs " link prefs} for how to configure

@endnode

@node prefs "Configuration"

                              Configuring Clipper


         Saving prefs also saves the Window Dimentions , selected page,
                    Edit status, and Selected List position

     To UN-Select a List just click the Page Gadget and item is De-selected

   either use the menus or the small popup gedget (lower Right above string)
                        to Hide or Show the Edit Gadgets


                   It's All pretty straight forward really :)

               Buble help Is all you should need to understand :)

                                  have a play


@endnode

@node hist "The Story so far"

 History
 -------

 Version 4.2
 increased Maximum Pages from 37 to 48 (suddenly i could :-\  )

 Version 4.1
 added an cli argument SCREEN=Name to open on screens (default is ActiveScreen)

 Version 4.0
 New Bubble was only opening on Workbench Screen (Fixed)

 Version 3.9
 Changed Screen title help to be Bubble Help :)

 Version 3.8
 made Clipper use S:ClipPrefs/ as default prefs dir.
 cleaned the code up a bit as it all seems to be working ok now.

 Version 3.7
 1 week after 3.5 , fixed a  few bugs (all i hope).


 Version 3.5 (12/12/99) 2:03pm
 here i start this version info. I'll only put a bit of info for 1.0 / 2.0

 a few major updates from 2.0 through to 3.5 including ..
 now has up to 37 pages
